Explain POM
In our automation framework, we follow a layered architecture mainly to separate responsibilities and reduce maintenance cost.
The Base layer handles all cross-cutting concerns like WebDriver lifecycle, configuration, and reporting.
The Page Object layer encapsulates UI structure and behavior — locators and actions stay there so UI changes don’t break tests.
The Test layer focuses only on business scenarios and assertions.
This structure allows us to scale tests, switch browsers, and absorb UI changes with minimal impact.
