Yes, the Main method can be overloaded in C#. However, the CLR will only consider specific signatures like static void Main(string[] args) or static int Main() as the entry point. Any overloaded versions are treated like normal methods and must be called explicitly.
This is similar to any method overloading, but special because Main has restrictions due to being the program entry point
