12.If two of your team has release?what would you do?
If two teams have releases at the same time, I would first analyze the priority, business impact, release risk, and criticality of both releases.
Based on that, I would allocate resources accordingly and ensure proper coordination between teams. If needed, I would personally support the high-priority or high-risk release while delegating experienced team members to support the other release.
My focus would be to ensure both releases are completed smoothly without impacting quality or timelines through proper planning, communication, and resource management
**********************************************************************
13.As tester would is necessary domain knowlege or requirement document to avoid bug leakage?
Yes, domain knowledge and requirement understanding are very important for a tester to avoid bug leakage.
Requirement documents help us understand the expected functionality and acceptance criteria, while domain knowledge helps us validate the application from a real business and user perspective.
With good understanding of both, we can identify edge cases, cover critical scenarios properly, and reduce the chances of defects reaching production.
